8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Docsumo and Tallyfy share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Api Connections, Scheduling, Conditional Logic. Where Docsumo pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Support and Error Handling and Ai Actions, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Docsumo holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Tallyfy scores 6/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Docsumo offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Tallyfy's starting price of $5/user/mo. Docsumo has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Tallyfy does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
